Global EPS Torque Sensor Market Insights
EPS Torque Sensor Market size was valued at USD 1.2 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 2.4 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 9.2% from 2024 to 2030.

EPS Torque Sensor Market Overview
The EPS Torque Sensor market was valued at USD 2.5 billion in 2024 and is expected to grow at a compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of 8.5% from 2025 to 2032, reaching an estimated market value of USD 5.3 billion by 2032. This growth is driven by the increasing demand for electronic power steering (EPS) systems in vehicles, as well as the growing emphasis on advanced automotive technologies for improved safety and fuel efficiency. The automotive industry, in particular, is witnessing a strong trend toward the integration of torque sensors to enhance vehicle handling, driver comfort, and steering precision.

